docs.lead_paragraph: A critic once described the performance of a popular English actress as giving the impression that she was playing the role of Nothing in "Much Ado About Nothing." Tom Prideaux means no such thing in the title of his biography of Ellen Terry. He means what Shaw meant in a letter to her of 1897: "I am convinced that with you a human relation is love or nothing."
